group.name: defines.command.group
group.doc: Do what your group wants you to do.

attack_area.name: defines.command.attack_area
attack_area.doc: Go to a place and attack what you see.

stop.name: defines.command.stop
stop.doc: Stop moving and stay where you are.

build_base.name: defines.command.build_base
build_base.doc: Go to a position and build a base there.

logical_and.name: defines.compound_command.logical_and
logical_and.doc: Fail on first failure. Only succeeds if all commands (executed one after another) succeed.

logical_or.name: defines.compound_command.logical_or
logical_or.doc: Succeed on first success. Only fails if all commands (executed one after another) fail.

return_last.name: defines.compound_command.return_last
return_last.doc: Execute all commands in sequence and fail or succeed depending on the return status of the last command.

ghost.name: defines.controllers.ghost
ghost.doc: Can't interact with the world, can only observe. Used in the multiplayer waiting-to-respawn screen.

character.name: defines.controllers.character
character.doc: The controller controls a character. This is the default controller in freeplay.

god.name: defines.controllers.god
god.doc: The controller isn't tied to a character. This is the default controller in sandbox.

editor.name: defines.controllers.editor
editor.doc: The Editor Controller near ultimate power to do almost anything in the game.

cutscene.name: defines.controllers.cutscene
cutscene.doc: The player can't interact with the world, and the camera pans around in a predefined manner.

spectator.name: defines.controllers.spectator
spectator.doc: Can't change anything in the world but can view anything.

none.name: defines.distraction.none
none.doc: Perform command even if someone attacks the unit.

by_enemy.name: defines.distraction.by_enemy
by_enemy.doc: Attack closer enemy entities with force.

by_anything.name: defines.distraction.by_anything
by_anything.doc: Attack closer enemy entities, including entities "built" by player (belts, inserters, chests).

not_plugged_in_electric_network.name: defines.entity_status.not_plugged_in_electric_network
not_plugged_in_electric_network.doc: Used by generators and solar panels.

no_input_fluid.name: defines.entity_status.no_input_fluid
no_input_fluid.doc: Used by boilers, fluid turrets and fluid energy sources: Boiler has no fluid to work with.

low_input_fluid.name: defines.entity_status.low_input_fluid
low_input_fluid.doc: Used by boilers and fluid turrets: Boiler still has some fluid but is about to run out.

full_output.name: defines.entity_status.full_output
full_output.doc: Used by crafting machines, boilers, burner energy sources and reactors: Reactor/burner has full burnt result inventory, boiler has full output fluidbox.

missing_required_fluid.name: defines.entity_status.missing_required_fluid
missing_required_fluid.doc: Used by mining drills when the mining fluid is missing.

waiting_for_space_in_destination.name: defines.entity_status.waiting_for_space_in_destination
waiting_for_space_in_destination.doc: Used by inserters and mining drills.

waiting_for_target_to_be_built.name: defines.entity_status.waiting_for_target_to_be_built
waiting_for_target_to_be_built.doc: Used by inserters targeting entity ghosts.

disabled.name: defines.entity_status.disabled
disabled.doc: Used by constant combinators: Combinator is turned off via switch in GUI.

always.name: defines.game_controller_interaction.always
always.doc: Game controller will always hover this element regardless of type or state.

never.name: defines.game_controller_interaction.never
never.doc: Never hover this element with a game controller.

normal.name: defines.game_controller_interaction.normal
normal.doc: Hover according to the element type and implementation.

if_redundant.name: defines.print_skip.if_redundant
if_redundant.doc: Print will be skipped if same text was recently printed (within last 60 ticks). Used by most game messages.

if_visible.name: defines.print_skip.if_visible
if_visible.doc: Print will be skipped if same text is still visible (printed within last 1152 ticks). Used by some notifications.

properties.undefined: prototypesA dictionary mapping all top-level prototypes by name to a list of their associated subtypes. This list is organized as a lookup table, meaning it maps the sub-prototype names to 0. As an example, defines.prototypes['entity'] looks like this: {furnace=0, inserter=0, container=0, ...}.

building_rocket.name: defines.rocket_silo_status.building_rocket
building_rocket.doc: The rocket silo is crafting rocket parts. When there are enough rocket parts, the silo will switch into the create_rocket state.

create_rocket.name: defines.rocket_silo_status.create_rocket
create_rocket.doc: The next state is lights_blinking_open. The rocket silo rocket entity gets created.

lights_blinking_open.name: defines.rocket_silo_status.lights_blinking_open
lights_blinking_open.doc: The next state is doors_opening. The rocket is getting prepared for launch.

doors_opening.name: defines.rocket_silo_status.doors_opening
doors_opening.doc: The next state is doors_opened. The rocket is getting prepared for launch.

doors_opened.name: defines.rocket_silo_status.doors_opened
doors_opened.doc: The next state is rocket_rising or if the rocket is destroyed in this state then the next state will be lights_blinking_close. The rocket is getting prepared for launch.

rocket_rising.name: defines.rocket_silo_status.rocket_rising
rocket_rising.doc: The next state is arms_advance or if the rocket is destroyed in this state then the next state will be lights_blinking_close. The rocket is getting prepared for launch.

arms_advance.name: defines.rocket_silo_status.arms_advance
arms_advance.doc: The next state is rocket_ready or if the rocket is destroyed in this state then the next state will be lights_blinking_close. The rocket is getting prepared for launch.

rocket_ready.name: defines.rocket_silo_status.rocket_ready
rocket_ready.doc: The rocket launch can be started by the player. When the launch is started, the silo switches into the launch_starting state.

engine_starting.name: defines.rocket_silo_status.engine_starting
engine_starting.doc: The next state is arms_retract or if the rocket is destroyed in this state then the next state will be lights_blinking_close. The rocket is getting launched.

arms_retract.name: defines.rocket_silo_status.arms_retract
arms_retract.doc: The next state is rocket_flying or if the rocket is destroyed in this state then the next state will be lights_blinking_close. The rocket is getting launched.

rocket_flying.name: defines.rocket_silo_status.rocket_flying
rocket_flying.doc: The next state is lights_blinking_close. The rocket is getting launched.

launch_started.name: defines.rocket_silo_status.launch_started
launch_started.doc: The next state is engine_starting or if the rocket is destroyed in this state then the next state will be lights_blinking_close. The rocket is getting launched.

path_lost.name: defines.train_state.path_lost
path_lost.doc: Had path and lost it -- must stop.

no_path.name: defines.train_state.no_path
no_path.doc: Has no path and is stopped.

manual_control_stop.name: defines.train_state.manual_control_stop
manual_control_stop.doc: Switched to manual control and has to stop.

manual_control.name: defines.train_state.manual_control
manual_control.doc: Can move if user explicitly sits in and rides the train.

destination_full.name: defines.train_state.destination_full
destination_full.doc: Same as no_path but all candidate train stops are full

allow_destroy_when_commands_fail.name: allow_destroy_when_commands_fail
allow_destroy_when_commands_fail.doc: If enabled, units that repeatedly fail to succeed at commands will be destroyed.
allow_destroy_when_commands_fail.short: If enabled, units that repeatedly fail to succeed at commands will be destroyed.

allow_try_return_to_spawner.name: allow_try_return_to_spawner
allow_try_return_to_spawner.doc: If enabled, units that have nothing else to do will attempt to return to a spawner.
allow_try_return_to_spawner.short: If enabled, units that have nothing else to do will attempt to return to a spawner.

do_separation.name: do_separation
do_separation.doc: If enabled, units will try to separate themselves from nearby friendly units.
do_separation.short: If enabled, units will try to separate themselves from nearby friendly units.

path_resolution_modifier.name: path_resolution_modifier
path_resolution_modifier.doc: Defines how coarse the pathfinder's grid is, where smaller values mean a coarser grid. Defaults to 0, which equals a resolution of 1x1 tiles, centered on tile centers. Values range from -8 to 8 inclusive, where each integer increment doubles/halves the resolution. So, a resolution of -8 equals a grid of 256x256 tiles, and a resolution of 8 equals 1/256 of a tile.
path_resolution_modifier.short: Defines how coarse the pathfinder's grid is, where smaller values mean a coarser grid. [...]

valid.name: valid
valid.doc: Is this object valid? This Lua object holds a reference to an object within the game engine. It is possible that the game-engine object is removed whilst a mod still holds the corresponding Lua object. If that happens, the object becomes invalid, i.e. this attribute will be false. Mods are advised to check for object validity if any change to the game state might have occurred between the creation of the Lua object and its access.

object_name.name: object_name
object_name.doc: The class name of this object. Available even when valid is false. For LuaStruct objects it may also be suffixed with a dotted path to a member of the struct.

on_init.name: on_init
on_init.doc: Register a function to be run on mod initialization. This is only called when a new save game is created or when a save file is loaded that previously didn't contain the mod. During it, the mod gets the chance to set up initial values that it will use for its lifetime. It has full access to LuaGameScript and the global table and can change anything about them that it deems appropriate. No other events will be raised for the mod until it has finished this step.
on_init.short: Register a function to be run on mod initialization. [...]

handler.name: handler
handler.doc: The handler for this event. Passing nil will unregister it.

on_load.name: on_load
on_load.doc: Register a function to be run on save load. This is only called for mods that have been part of the save previously, or for players connecting to a running multiplayer session.
on_load.short: Register a function to be run on save load. [...]

handler.name: handler
handler.doc: The handler for this event. Passing nil will unregister it.

on_configuration_changed.name: on_configuration_changed
on_configuration_changed.doc: Register a function to be run when mod configuration changes. This is called when the game version or any mod version changed, when any mod was added or removed, when a startup setting has changed, when any prototypes have been added or removed, or when a migration was applied. It allows the mod to make any changes it deems appropriate to both the data structures in its global table or to the game state through LuaGameScript.
on_configuration_changed.short: Register a function to be run when mod configuration changes. [...]

handler.name: handler
handler.doc: The handler for this event. Passing nil will unregister it.

on_event.name: on_event
on_event.doc: Register a handler to run on the specified event(s). Each mod can only register once for every event, as any additional registration will overwrite the previous one. This holds true even if different filters are used for subsequent registrations.
on_event.short: Register a handler to run on the specified event(s). [...]

event.name: event
event.type: defines.events or string or array[defines.events or string]
event.doc: The event(s) or custom-input to invoke the handler on.

handler.name: handler
handler.doc: The handler for this event. Passing nil will unregister it.

filters.name: filters
filters.doc: The filters for this event. Can only be used when registering for individual events.

on_nth_tick.name: on_nth_tick
on_nth_tick.doc: Register a handler to run every nth-tick(s). When the game is on tick 0 it will trigger all registered handlers.
on_nth_tick.short: Register a handler to run every nth-tick(s). [...]

tick.name: tick
tick.doc: The nth-tick(s) to invoke the handler on. Passing nil as the only parameter will unregister all nth-tick handlers.

handler.name: handler
handler.doc: The handler to run. Passing nil will unregister it for the provided nth-tick(s).

register_on_entity_destroyed.name: register_on_entity_destroyed
register_on_entity_destroyed.doc: Registers an entity so that after it's destroyed, on_entity_destroyed is called. Once an entity is registered, it stays registered until it is actually destroyed, even through save/load cycles. The registration is global across all mods, meaning once one mod registers an entity, all mods listening to on_entity_destroyed will receive the event when it is destroyed. Registering the same entity multiple times will still only fire the destruction event once, and will return the same registration number. Returns: The registration number. It is used to identify the entity in the on_entity_destroyed event.
register_on_entity_destroyed.short: Registers an entity so that after it's destroyed, on_entity_destroyed is called. [...]

register_metatable.name: register_metatable
register_metatable.doc: Register a metatable to have linkage recorded and restored when saving/loading. The metatable itself will not be saved. Instead, only the linkage to a registered metatable is saved, and the metatable registered under that name will be used when loading the table.
register_metatable.short: Register a metatable to have linkage recorded and restored when saving/loading. [...]

name.name: name
name.doc: The name of this metatable. Names must be unique per mod.

generate_event_name.name: generate_event_name

generate_event_name.short: Generate a new, unique event ID that can be used to raise custom events with LuaBootstrap::raise_event.

circuit_connector.name: circuit_connector
circuit_connector.doc: The connector to get circuit network for. Must be specified for entities with more than one circuit network connector.

get_merged_signal.name: get_merged_signal
get_merged_signal.doc: Read a single signal from the combined circuit networks. Returns: The current value of the signal.
get_merged_signal.short: Read a single signal from the combined circuit networks.

circuit_connector.name: circuit_connector
circuit_connector.doc: The connector to get signals for. Must be specified for entities with more than one circuit network connector.

get_merged_signals.name: get_merged_signals
get_merged_signals.doc: The merged circuit network signals or nil if there are no signals. Returns: The sum of signals on both the red and green networks, or nil if it doesn't have a circuit connector.
get_merged_signals.short: The merged circuit network signals or nil if there are no signals.

circuit_connector.name: circuit_connector
circuit_connector.doc: The connector to get signals for. Must be specified for entities with more than one circuit network connector.

supports_backer_name.name: supports_backer_name
supports_backer_name.doc: Whether this entity supports a backer name.
supports_backer_name.short: Whether this entity supports a backer name.

copy_settings.name: copy_settings
copy_settings.doc: Copies settings from the given entity onto this entity. Returns: Any items removed from this entity as a result of copying the settings.
copy_settings.short: Copies settings from the given entity onto this entity.

by_player.name: by_player
by_player.doc: If provided, the copying is done 'as' this player and on_entity_settings_pasted is triggered.

get_logistic_point.name: get_logistic_point
get_logistic_point.doc: Gets all the LuaLogisticPoints that this entity owns. Optionally returns only the point specified by the index parameter.
get_logistic_point.short: Gets all the LuaLogisticPoints that this entity owns. [...]

index.name: index
index.doc: If provided, only returns the LuaLogisticPoint specified by this index.

play_note.name: play_note
play_note.doc: Plays a note with the given instrument and note. Returns: Whether the request is valid. The sound may or may not be played depending on polyphony settings.
play_note.short: Plays a note with the given instrument and note.

connect_rolling_stock.name: connect_rolling_stock
connect_rolling_stock.doc: Connects the rolling stock in the given direction. Returns: Whether any connection was made
connect_rolling_stock.short: Connects the rolling stock in the given direction.

disconnect_rolling_stock.name: disconnect_rolling_stock
disconnect_rolling_stock.doc: Tries to disconnect this rolling stock in the given direction. Returns: If anything was disconnected
disconnect_rolling_stock.short: Tries to disconnect this rolling stock in the given direction.

update_connections.name: update_connections
update_connections.doc: Reconnect loader, beacon, cliff and mining drill connections to entities that might have been teleported out or in by the script. The game doesn't do this automatically as we don't want to loose performance by checking this in normal games.
update_connections.short: Reconnect loader, beacon, cliff and mining drill connections to entities that might have been teleported out or in by the script. [...]

get_recipe.name: get_recipe
get_recipe.doc: Current recipe being assembled by this machine, if any.
get_recipe.short: Current recipe being assembled by this machine, if any.

set_recipe.name: set_recipe
set_recipe.doc: Sets the given recipe in this assembly machine. Returns: Any items removed from this entity as a result of setting the recipe.
set_recipe.short: Sets the given recipe in this assembly machine.

recipe.name: recipe
recipe.doc: The new recipe. Writing nil clears the recipe, if any.

rotate.name: rotate
rotate.doc: Rotates this entity as if the player rotated it. Returns: Count of spilled items indexed by their prototype names if spill_items was true.
rotate.short: Rotates this entity as if the player rotated it.
rotate.member: rotate{reverse?=…, by_player?=…, spill_items?=…, enable_looted?=…, force?=…}  → boolean, dictionary[string → uint]?

reverse.name: reverse
reverse.doc: If true, rotate the entity in the counter-clockwise direction.

by_player.name: by_player
by_player.doc: If not specified, the on_player_rotated_entity event will not be fired.

spill_items.name: spill_items
spill_items.doc: If the player is not given should extra items be spilled or returned as a second return value from this.

enable_looted.name: enable_looted
enable_looted.doc: When true, each spilled item will be flagged with the LuaEntity::to_be_looted flag.

force.name: force
force.doc: When provided the spilled items will be marked for deconstruction by this force.

on_player_rotated_entity?.name: on_player_rotated_entity?
on_player_rotated_entity?.doc: Raised if the by_player argument was given and the rotation was successful.

get_driver.name: get_driver
get_driver.doc: Gets the driver of this vehicle if any. Returns: nil if the vehicle contains no driver. To check if there's a passenger see LuaEntity::get_passenger.
get_driver.short: Gets the driver of this vehicle if any.

set_driver.name: set_driver
set_driver.doc: Sets the driver of this vehicle.
set_driver.short: Sets the driver of this vehicle.

driver.name: driver
driver.doc: The new driver. Writing nil ejects the current driver, if any.

get_passenger.name: get_passenger
get_passenger.doc: Gets the passenger of this car or spidertron if any. Returns: nil if the vehicle contains no passenger. To check if there's a driver see LuaEntity::get_driver.
get_passenger.short: Gets the passenger of this car or spidertron if any.

set_passenger.name: set_passenger
set_passenger.doc: Sets the passenger of this car or spidertron.
set_passenger.short: Sets the passenger of this car or spidertron.

passenger.name: passenger
passenger.doc: The new passenger. Writing nil ejects the current passenger, if any.

is_connected_to_electric_network.name: is_connected_to_electric_network
is_connected_to_electric_network.doc: Returns true if this entity produces or consumes electricity and is connected to an electric network that has at least one entity that can produce power.
is_connected_to_electric_network.short: Returns true if this entity produces or consumes electricity and is connected to an electric network that has at least one entity that can produce power.

get_train_stop_trains.name: get_train_stop_trains
get_train_stop_trains.doc: The trains scheduled to stop at this train stop.
get_train_stop_trains.short: The trains scheduled to stop at this train stop.

get_stopped_train.name: get_stopped_train
get_stopped_train.doc: The train currently stopped at this train stop, if any.
get_stopped_train.short: The train currently stopped at this train stop, if any.

clone.name: clone
clone.doc: Clones this entity. Returns: The cloned entity or nil if this entity can't be cloned/can't be cloned to the given location.

position.name: position
position.doc: The destination position

surface.name: surface
surface.doc: The destination surface

create_build_effect_smoke.name: create_build_effect_smoke
create_build_effect_smoke.doc: If false, the building effect smoke will not be shown around the new entity.

on_entity_cloned?.name: on_entity_cloned?
on_entity_cloned?.doc: Raised if the entity was successfully cloned.

get_fluid_count.name: get_fluid_count
get_fluid_count.doc: Get the amount of all or some fluid in this entity.
get_fluid_count.short: Get the amount of all or some fluid in this entity.

fluid.name: fluid
fluid.doc: Prototype name of the fluid to count. If not specified, count all fluids.

get_fluid_contents.name: get_fluid_contents
get_fluid_contents.doc: Get amounts of all fluids in this entity. Returns: The amounts, indexed by fluid names.
get_fluid_contents.short: Get amounts of all fluids in this entity.

remove_fluid.name: remove_fluid
remove_fluid.doc: Remove fluid from this entity. Returns: Amount of fluid actually removed.
remove_fluid.member: remove_fluid{name=…, amount=…, minimum_temperature?=…, maximum_temperature?=…, temperature?=…}  → double

insert_fluid.name: insert_fluid
insert_fluid.doc: Insert fluid into this entity. Fluidbox is chosen automatically. Returns: Amount of fluid actually inserted.

clear_fluid_inside.name: clear_fluid_inside
clear_fluid_inside.doc: Remove all fluids from this entity.
clear_fluid_inside.short: Remove all fluids from this entity.

get_beam_source.name: get_beam_source
get_beam_source.doc: Get the source of this beam.
get_beam_source.short: Get the source of this beam.

set_beam_source.name: set_beam_source
set_beam_source.doc: Set the source of this beam.
set_beam_source.short: Set the source of this beam.

get_beam_target.name: get_beam_target
get_beam_target.doc: Get the target of this beam.
get_beam_target.short: Get the target of this beam.

set_beam_target.name: set_beam_target
set_beam_target.doc: Set the target of this beam.
set_beam_target.short: Set the target of this beam.

get_health_ratio.name: get_health_ratio
get_health_ratio.doc: The health ratio of this entity between 1 and 0 (for full health and no health respectively). Returns: nil if this entity doesn't have health.
get_health_ratio.short: The health ratio of this entity between 1 and 0 (for full health and no health respectively).

create_build_effect_smoke.name: create_build_effect_smoke
create_build_effect_smoke.doc: Creates the same smoke that is created when you place a building by hand. You can play the building sound to go with it by using LuaSurface::play_sound, eg: entity.surface.play_sound{path="entity-build/"..entity.prototype.name, position=entity.position}
create_build_effect_smoke.short: Creates the same smoke that is created when you place a building by hand. [...]

release_from_spawner.name: release_from_spawner
release_from_spawner.doc: Release the unit from the spawner which spawned it. This allows the spawner to continue spawning additional units.
release_from_spawner.short: Release the unit from the spawner which spawned it. [...]

toggle_equipment_movement_bonus.name: toggle_equipment_movement_bonus
toggle_equipment_movement_bonus.doc: Toggle this entity's equipment movement bonus. Does nothing if the entity does not have an equipment grid.
toggle_equipment_movement_bonus.short: Toggle this entity's equipment movement bonus. [...]

can_shoot.name: can_shoot
can_shoot.doc: Whether this character can shoot the given entity or position.
can_shoot.short: Whether this character can shoot the given entity or position.

start_fading_out.name: start_fading_out
start_fading_out.doc: Only works if the entity is a speech-bubble, with an "effect" defined in its wrapper_flow_style. Starts animating the opacity of the speech bubble towards zero, and destroys the entity when it hits zero.
start_fading_out.short: Only works if the entity is a speech-bubble, with an "effect" defined in its wrapper_flow_style. [...]

get_upgrade_target.name: get_upgrade_target
get_upgrade_target.doc: Returns the new entity prototype. Returns: nil if this entity is not marked for upgrade.

get_upgrade_direction.name: get_upgrade_direction
get_upgrade_direction.doc: Returns the new entity direction after upgrading. Returns: nil if this entity is not marked for upgrade.
get_upgrade_direction.short: Returns the new entity direction after upgrading.

get_damage_to_be_taken.name: get_damage_to_be_taken
get_damage_to_be_taken.doc: Returns the amount of damage to be taken by this entity. Returns: nil if this entity does not have health.
get_damage_to_be_taken.short: Returns the amount of damage to be taken by this entity.

deplete.name: deplete
deplete.doc: Depletes and destroys this resource entity.
deplete.short: Depletes and destroys this resource entity.

mine.name: mine
mine.doc: Mines this entity. Returns: Whether mining succeeded.

inventory.name: inventory
inventory.doc: If provided the item(s) will be transferred into this inventory. If provided, this must be an inventory created with LuaGameScript::create_inventory or be a basic inventory owned by some entity.

force.name: force
force.doc: If true, when the item(s) don't fit into the given inventory the entity is force mined. If false, the mining operation fails when there isn't enough room to transfer all of the items into the inventory. Defaults to false. This is ignored and acts as true if no inventory is provided.

raise_destroyed.name: raise_destroyed
raise_destroyed.doc: If true, script_raised_destroy will be raised. Defaults to true.

ignore_minable.name: ignore_minable
ignore_minable.doc: If true, the minable state of the entity is ignored. Defaults to false. If false, an entity that isn't minable (set as not-minable in the prototype or isn't minable for other reasons) will fail to be mined.

script_raised_destroy?.name: script_raised_destroy?
script_raised_destroy?.doc: Raised if the raise_destroyed flag was set and the entity was successfully mined.

spawn_decorations.name: spawn_decorations
spawn_decorations.doc: Triggers spawn_decoration actions defined in the entity prototype or does nothing if entity is not "turret" or "unit-spawner".
spawn_decorations.short: Triggers spawn_decoration actions defined in the entity prototype or does nothing if entity is not "turret" or "unit-spawner".

can_wires_reach.name: can_wires_reach
can_wires_reach.doc: Can wires reach between these entities.
can_wires_reach.short: Can wires reach between these entities.

get_connected_rolling_stock.name: get_connected_rolling_stock
get_connected_rolling_stock.doc: Gets rolling stock connected to the given end of this stock. Returns: The rail direction of the connected rolling stock if any.
get_connected_rolling_stock.short: Gets rolling stock connected to the given end of this stock.

is_registered_for_construction.name: is_registered_for_construction
is_registered_for_construction.doc: Is this entity or tile ghost or item request proxy registered for construction? If false, it means a construction robot has been dispatched to build the entity, or it is not an entity that can be constructed.
is_registered_for_construction.short: Is this entity or tile ghost or item request proxy registered for construction? [...]

is_registered_for_deconstruction.name: is_registered_for_deconstruction
is_registered_for_deconstruction.doc: Is this entity registered for deconstruction with this force? If false, it means a construction robot has been dispatched to deconstruct it, or it is not marked for deconstruction. The complexity is effectively O(1) - it depends on the number of objects targeting this entity which should be small enough.
is_registered_for_deconstruction.short: Is this entity registered for deconstruction with this force? [...]

force.name: force
force.doc: The force construction manager to check.

is_registered_for_upgrade.name: is_registered_for_upgrade
is_registered_for_upgrade.doc: Is this entity registered for upgrade? If false, it means a construction robot has been dispatched to upgrade it, or it is not marked for upgrade. This is worst-case O(N) complexity where N is the current number of things in the upgrade queue.
is_registered_for_upgrade.short: Is this entity registered for upgrade? [...]

is_registered_for_repair.name: is_registered_for_repair
is_registered_for_repair.doc: Is this entity registered for repair? If false, it means a construction robot has been dispatched to upgrade it, or it is not damaged. This is worst-case O(N) complexity where N is the current number of things in the repair queue.
is_registered_for_repair.short: Is this entity registered for repair? [...]

add_autopilot_destination.name: add_autopilot_destination
add_autopilot_destination.doc: Adds the given position to this spidertron's autopilot's queue of destinations.
add_autopilot_destination.short: Adds the given position to this spidertron's autopilot's queue of destinations.

position.name: position
position.doc: The position the spidertron should move to.

connect_linked_belts.name: connect_linked_belts
connect_linked_belts.doc: Connects current linked belt with another one.
connect_linked_belts.short: Connects current linked belt with another one. [...]

neighbour.name: neighbour
neighbour.doc: Another linked belt or entity ghost containing linked belt to connect or nil to disconnect

disconnect_linked_belts.name: disconnect_linked_belts
disconnect_linked_belts.doc: Disconnects linked belt from its neighbour.
disconnect_linked_belts.short: Disconnects linked belt from its neighbour.

stop_spider.name: stop_spider
stop_spider.doc: Sets the speed of the given SpiderVehicle to zero. Notably does not clear its autopilot_destination, which it will continue moving towards if set.
stop_spider.short: Sets the speed of the given SpiderVehicle to zero. [...]

get_beacons.name: get_beacons
get_beacons.doc: Returns a table with all beacons affecting this effect receiver. Can only be used when the entity has an effect receiver (AssemblingMachine, Furnace, Lab, MiningDrills)
get_beacons.short: Returns a table with all beacons affecting this effect receiver. [...]

get_beacon_effect_receivers.name: get_beacon_effect_receivers
get_beacon_effect_receivers.doc: Returns a table with all entities affected by this beacon
get_beacon_effect_receivers.short: Returns a table with all entities affected by this beacon

help.name: help
help.doc: All methods and properties that this object supports.
help.short: All methods and properties that this object supports.

name.name: name
name.doc: Name of the entity prototype. E.g. "inserter" or "filter-inserter".

ghost_name.name: ghost_name
ghost_name.doc: Name of the entity or tile contained in this ghost
ghost_name.short: Name of the entity or tile contained in this ghost

ghost_localised_name.name: ghost_localised_name
ghost_localised_name.doc: Localised name of the entity or tile contained in this ghost.
ghost_localised_name.short: Localised name of the entity or tile contained in this ghost.

type.name: type
type.doc: The entity prototype type of this entity.
type.short: The entity prototype type of this entity.

ghost_type.name: ghost_type
ghost_type.doc: The prototype type of the entity or tile contained in this ghost.
ghost_type.short: The prototype type of the entity or tile contained in this ghost.

active.name: active
active.doc: Deactivating an entity will stop all its operations (car will stop moving, inserters will stop working, fish will stop moving etc).
active.short: Deactivating an entity will stop all its operations (car will stop moving, inserters will stop working, fish will stop moving etc).

destructible.name: destructible
destructible.doc: If set to false, this entity can't be damaged and won't be attacked automatically. It can however still be mined.
destructible.short: If set to false, this entity can't be damaged and won't be attacked automatically. [...]

minable.name: minable
minable.doc: Not minable entities can still be destroyed.

rotatable.name: rotatable
rotatable.doc: When entity is not to be rotatable (inserter, transport belt etc), it can't be rotated by player using the R key.
rotatable.short: When entity is not to be rotatable (inserter, transport belt etc), it can't be rotated by player using the R key.

operable.name: operable
operable.doc: Player can't open gui of this entity and he can't quick insert/input stuff in to the entity when it is not operable.
operable.short: Player can't open gui of this entity and he can't quick insert/input stuff in to the entity when it is not operable.

health.name: health
health.doc: The current health of the entity, if any. Health is automatically clamped to be between 0 and max health (inclusive). Entities with a health of 0 can not be attacked.
health.short: The current health of the entity, if any. [...]

direction.name: direction
direction.doc: The current direction this entity is facing.
direction.short: The current direction this entity is facing.

supports_direction.name: supports_direction
supports_direction.doc: Whether the entity has direction. When it is false for this entity, it will always return north direction when asked for.

orientation.name: orientation
orientation.doc: The smooth orientation of this entity.
orientation.short: The smooth orientation of this entity.

relative_turret_orientation.name: relative_turret_orientation
relative_turret_orientation.doc: The relative orientation of the vehicle turret, artillery turret, artillery wagon. nil if this entity isn't a vehicle with a vehicle turret or artillery turret/wagon.
relative_turret_orientation.short: The relative orientation of the vehicle turret, artillery turret, artillery wagon. [...]

torso_orientation.name: torso_orientation
torso_orientation.doc: The torso orientation of this spider vehicle.
torso_orientation.short: The torso orientation of this spider vehicle.

initial_amount.name: initial_amount
initial_amount.doc: Count of initial resource units contained. nil if this is not an infinite resource.
initial_amount.short: Count of initial resource units contained. [...]

effectivity_modifier.name: effectivity_modifier
effectivity_modifier.doc: Multiplies the acceleration the vehicle can create for one unit of energy. Defaults to 1.
effectivity_modifier.short: Multiplies the acceleration the vehicle can create for one unit of energy. [...]

driver_is_gunner.name: driver_is_gunner
driver_is_gunner.doc: Whether the driver of this car or spidertron is the gunner. If false, the passenger is the gunner. nil if this is neither a car or a spidertron.
driver_is_gunner.short: Whether the driver of this car or spidertron is the gunner. [...]

vehicle_automatic_targeting_parameters.name: vehicle_automatic_targeting_parameters
vehicle_automatic_targeting_parameters.doc: Read when this spidertron auto-targets enemies
vehicle_automatic_targeting_parameters.short: Read when this spidertron auto-targets enemies

speed.name: speed
speed.doc: The current speed if this is a car, rolling stock, projectile or spidertron, or the maximum speed if this is a unit. The speed is in tiles per tick. nil if this is not a car, rolling stock, unit, projectile or spidertron.
speed.short: The current speed if this is a car, rolling stock, projectile or spidertron, or the maximum speed if this is a unit. [...]

effective_speed.name: effective_speed
effective_speed.doc: The current speed of this unit in tiles per tick, taking into account any walking speed modifier given by the tile the unit is standing on. nil if this is not a unit.
effective_speed.short: The current speed of this unit in tiles per tick, taking into account any walking speed modifier given by the tile the unit is standing on. [...]

prototype.name: prototype
prototype.doc: The entity prototype of this entity.
prototype.short: The entity prototype of this entity.

ghost_prototype.name: ghost_prototype
ghost_prototype.doc: The prototype of the entity or tile contained in this ghost.
ghost_prototype.short: The prototype of the entity or tile contained in this ghost.

drop_position.name: drop_position
drop_position.doc: Position where the entity puts its stuff.
drop_position.short: Position where the entity puts its stuff.

pickup_position.name: pickup_position
pickup_position.doc: Where the inserter will pick up items from.
pickup_position.short: Where the inserter will pick up items from.

drop_target.name: drop_target
drop_target.doc: The entity this entity is putting its items to. If there are multiple possible entities at the drop-off point, writing to this attribute allows a mod to choose which one to drop off items to. The entity needs to collide with the tile box under the drop-off position. nil if there is no entity to put items to, or if this is not an entity that puts items somewhere.
drop_target.short: The entity this entity is putting its items to. [...]

pickup_target.name: pickup_target
pickup_target.doc: The entity this inserter will attempt to pick up items from. If there are multiple possible entities at the pick-up point, writing to this attribute allows a mod to choose which one to pick up items from. The entity needs to collide with the tile box under the pick-up position. nil if there is no entity to pull items from.
pickup_target.short: The entity this inserter will attempt to pick up items from. [...]

selected_gun_index.name: selected_gun_index
selected_gun_index.doc: Index of the currently selected weapon slot of this character, car, or spidertron. nil if this entity doesn't have guns.
selected_gun_index.short: Index of the currently selected weapon slot of this character, car, or spidertron. [...]

energy.name: energy
energy.doc: Energy stored in the entity (heat in furnace, energy stored in electrical devices etc.). always 0 for entities that don't have the concept of energy stored inside.
energy.short: Energy stored in the entity (heat in furnace, energy stored in electrical devices etc.). [...]

temperature.name: temperature
temperature.doc: The temperature of this entity's heat energy source. nil if this entity does not use a heat energy source.
temperature.short: The temperature of this entity's heat energy source. [...]

previous_recipe.name: previous_recipe
previous_recipe.doc: The previous recipe this furnace was using, if any.
previous_recipe.short: The previous recipe this furnace was using, if any.

held_stack.name: held_stack
held_stack.doc: The item stack currently held in an inserter's hand.
held_stack.short: The item stack currently held in an inserter's hand.

train.name: train
train.doc: The train this rolling stock belongs to, if any. nil if this is not a rolling stock.
train.short: The train this rolling stock belongs to, if any. [...]

neighbours.name: neighbours
neighbours.doc: A list of neighbours for certain types of entities. Applies to electric poles, power switches, underground belts, walls, gates, reactors, cliffs, and pipe-connectable entities.
neighbours.short: A list of neighbours for certain types of entities. [...]
neighbours.member: neighbours  :: dictionary[string → array[LuaEntity]] or array[array[LuaEntity]] or LuaEntity Read

belt_neighbours.name: belt_neighbours

belt_neighbours.short: The belt connectable neighbours of this belt connectable entity. [...]

inputs.name: inputs

outputs.name: outputs
outputs.doc: Array of transport belt connectable entities.

backer_name.name: backer_name
backer_name.doc: The backer name assigned to this entity. Entities that support backer names are labs, locomotives, radars, roboports, and train stops. nil if this entity doesn't support backer names.

entity_label.name: entity_label

time_to_live.name: time_to_live
time_to_live.doc: The ticks left before a ghost, combat robot, highlight box, smoke with trigger or sticker is destroyed.
time_to_live.short: The ticks left before a ghost, combat robot, highlight box, smoke with trigger or sticker is destroyed. [...]

color.name: color
color.doc: The color of this character, rolling stock, train stop, car, spider-vehicle, flying text, corpse or simple-entity-with-owner. nil if this entity doesn't use custom colors.
color.short: The color of this character, rolling stock, train stop, car, spider-vehicle, flying text, corpse or simple-entity-with-owner. [...]

text.name: text

text.short: The text of this flying-text entity.

signal_state.name: signal_state

chain_signal_state.name: chain_signal_state

chain_signal_state.short: The state of this chain signal.

to_be_looted.short: Will this entity be picked up automatically when the player walks over it?

crafting_speed.name: crafting_speed

bonus_progress.name: bonus_progress
bonus_progress.doc: The current productivity bonus progress, as a number in range [0, 1].
bonus_progress.short: The current productivity bonus progress, as a number in range [0, 1].

productivity_bonus.name: productivity_bonus
productivity_bonus.doc: The productivity bonus of this entity.
productivity_bonus.short: The productivity bonus of this entity.

pollution_bonus.name: pollution_bonus
pollution_bonus.doc: The pollution bonus of this entity.
pollution_bonus.short: The pollution bonus of this entity.

speed_bonus.name: speed_bonus
speed_bonus.doc: The speed bonus of this entity.

Mods are advised to check for object validity if any change to the game state might have occurred between the creation of the Lua object and its access.

take_screenshot.member: take_screenshot{player?=…, by_player?=…, surface?=…, position?=…, resolution?=…, zoom?=…, path?=…, show_gui?=…, show_entity_info?=…, show_cursor_building_preview?=…, anti_alias?=…, quality?=…, allow_in_replay?=…, daytime?=…, water_tick?=…, force_render?=…}

player.name: player
player.doc: The player to focus on. Defaults to the local player.

by_player.name: by_player
by_player.doc: If defined, the screenshot will only be taken for this player.

surface.name: surface
surface.doc: If defined, the screenshot will be taken on this surface.

position.name: position
position.doc: If defined, the screenshot will be centered on this position. Otherwise, the screenshot will center on player.

resolution.name: resolution
resolution.doc: The maximum allowed resolution is 16384x16384 (8192x8192 when anti_alias is true), but the maximum recommended resolution is 4096x4096 (resp. 2048x2048). The x value of the position is used as the width, the y value as the height.

zoom.name: zoom
zoom.doc: The map zoom to take the screenshot at. Defaults to 1.

path.name: path
path.doc: The name of the image file. It should include a file extension indicating the desired format. Supports .png, .jpg /.jpeg, .tga and .bmp. Providing a directory path (ex. "save/here/screenshot.png") will create the necessary folder structure in script-output. Defaults to "screenshot.png".

show_gui.name: show_gui
show_gui.doc: Whether to include GUIs in the screenshot or not. Defaults to false.

show_entity_info.name: show_entity_info
show_entity_info.doc: Whether to include entity info ("Alt mode") or not. Defaults to false.

show_cursor_building_preview.name: show_cursor_building_preview
show_cursor_building_preview.doc: When true and when player is specified, the building preview for the item in the player's cursor will also be rendered. Defaults to false.

anti_alias.name: anti_alias
anti_alias.doc: Whether to render in double resolution and downscale the result (including GUI). Defaults to false.

quality.name: quality
quality.doc: The .jpg render quality as a percentage (from 0% to 100% inclusive), if used. A lower value means a more compressed image. Defaults to 80.

allow_in_replay.name: allow_in_replay
allow_in_replay.doc: Whether to save the screenshot even during replay playback. Defaults to false.

daytime.name: daytime
daytime.doc: Overrides the current surface daytime for the duration of screenshot rendering.

water_tick.name: water_tick
water_tick.doc: Overrides the tick of water animation, if animated water is enabled.

force_render.name: force_render
force_render.doc: Screenshot requests are processed in between game update and render. The game may skip rendering (ie. drop frames) if the previous frame has not finished rendering or the game simulation starts to fall below 60 updates per second. If force_render is set to true, the game won't drop frames and process the screenshot request at the end of the update in which the request was created. This is not honored on multiplayer clients that are catching up to server. Defaults to false.

set_wait_for_screenshots_to_finish.name: set_wait_for_screenshots_to_finish
set_wait_for_screenshots_to_finish.doc: Forces the screenshot saving system to wait until all queued screenshots have been written to disk.
set_wait_for_screenshots_to_finish.short: Forces the screenshot saving system to wait until all queued screenshots have been written to disk.

request_train_path.member: request_train_path{goals=…, in_chain_signal_section?=…, train?=…, type?=…, return_path?=…, from_front?=…, allow_path_within_segment_front?=…, from_back?=…, allow_path_within_segment_back?=…, search_direction?=…, steps_limit?=…}  → TrainPathFinderPathResult or TrainPathAnyGoalResult or TrainPathAllGoalsResult

in_chain_signal_section.name: in_chain_signal_section
in_chain_signal_section.doc: Defaults to false. If set to true, pathfinder will not return a path that cannot have its beginning immediately reserved. A path that cannot have its beginning immediately reserved could cause a train to stop inside of an intersection.

train.name: train
train.doc: Mandatory if from_front and from_back are not provided, optional otherwise. Selects a context for the pathfinder to decide which train to exclude from penalties and which signals are considered possible to reacquire. If from_front and from_back are not provided, then it is also used to collect front and back ends for the search

type.name: type
type.doc: Request type. Determines the return type of the method. Defaults to "path".

return_path.name: return_path
return_path.doc: Only relevant if request type is "path". Returning a full path is expensive due to multiple LuaEntity created. In order for path to be returned, true must be provided here. Defaults to false in which case a path will not be provided.

from_front.name: from_front
from_front.doc: Manually provided starting front of the train.

allow_path_within_segment_front.name: allow_path_within_segment_front
allow_path_within_segment_front.doc: Only relevant if from_front is given. Defaults to true. Providing false will cause the pathfinder to reject a path that starts on front and ends within the same segment as the path would be too short to provide correct alignment with a goal.

from_back.name: from_back

allow_path_within_segment_back.name: allow_path_within_segment_back

waypoints.doc: List of waypoints for the cutscene controller. This parameter is mandatory when type is defines.controllers.cutscene.

start_zoom.doc: If specified and type is defines.controllers.cutscene, the cutscene will start at this zoom level. If not given the start zoom will be the players zoom.

final_transition_time.doc: If specified and type is defines.controllers.cutscene, it is the time in ticks it will take for the camera to pan from the final waypoint back to the starting position. If not given the camera will not pan back to the start position/zoom.

chart_mode_cutoff.name: chart_mode_cutoff
chart_mode_cutoff.doc: If specified and type is defines.controllers.cutscene, the game will switch to chart-mode (map zoomed out) rendering when the zoom level is less than this value.

valid.doc: Is this object valid? This Lua object holds a reference to an object within the game engine. It is possible that the game-engine object is removed whilst a mod still holds the corresponding Lua object. If that happens, the object becomes invalid, i.e. this attribute will be false. Mods are advised to check for object validity if any change to the game state might have occurred between the creation of the Lua object and its access.

valid.doc: Is this object valid? This Lua object holds a reference to an object within the game engine. It is possible that the game-engine object is removed whilst a mod still holds the corresponding Lua object. If that happens, the object becomes invalid, i.e. this attribute will be false. valid.doc: Is this object valid? This Lua object holds a reference to an object within the game engine. It is possible that the game-engine object is removed whilst a mod still holds the corresponding Lua object. If that happens, the object becomes invalid, i.e. this attribute will be false. Mods are advised to check for object validity if any change to the game state might have occurred between the creation of the Lua object and its access.

path_resolution_modifier.name: path_resolution_modifier
path_resolution_modifier.doc: Defines how coarse the pathfinder's grid is, where smaller values mean a coarser grid. Defaults to 0, which equals a resolution of 1x1 tiles, centered on tile centers. Values range from -8 to 8 inclusive, where each integer increment doubles/halves the resolution. So, a resolution of -8 equals a grid of 256x256 tiles, and a resolution of 8 equals 1/256 of a tile.
